Vite + React + TypeScript on Cloudflare Pages.

## Getting started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev          # Vite (5173) + wrangler pages dev (8788) side-by-side
```

Open http://localhost:8788 — wrangler serves Functions and proxies static
asset requests to Vite. Vite's HMR works through the proxy.

## Deploy

First-time setup (Cloudflare API token + Pages project):

```bash
flint auth init      # one-time, stores ~/.config/flint/credentials
flint configure      # creates the Pages project + any KV/R2 declared in wrangler.toml
```

Subsequent deploys:

```bash
flint deploy         # pre-flight (lint / typecheck / test / build) then wrangler pages deploy
```

Or via npm:

```bash
npm run build
npm run deploy       # = wrangler pages deploy
```

## Commands

```text
npm run dev          # local dev (Vite + wrangler pages dev)
npm run build        # tsc -b + vite build
npm run lint         # eslint
npm test             # vitest
npm run deploy       # build + wrangler pages deploy
npm run logs         # tail Pages deployment logs
npm run deployments  # list recent deployments
```

## Configuration

- `wrangler.toml` — Cloudflare Pages config (KV / R2 / secrets declarations)
- `public/_headers` — response headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- `public/_routes.json` — Pages Function routing scope
- `.dev.vars` — local environment variables (gitignored; managed by Flint)
- `.dev.vars.example` — documented stubs for new contributors

## Add resources

```bash
flint add kv  CACHE_KV       # appends [[kv_namespaces]] block
flint add r2  BACKUPS        # appends [[r2_buckets]] block
flint add secret API_KEY     # adds .dev.vars.example stub + pushes via wrangler
```

## Token rotation

```bash
flint auth status            # check token + account
flint auth doctor            # probe each required scope
flint auth rotate            # walk through replacement
```
